text: Nesorohyla is a genus of frogs with exactly one species in it. It is in the family Hylidae. The species is Nesorohyla kanaima, also named the Kanaima treefrog. It lives in Guyana. Scientists think it could also live in Brazil and Venezuela. It lives in subtropical and tropical forests, both near sea level and in the mountains, and rivers. ==References== Category:Frogs of South America
title: Nesorohyla
